number = str()
largest = 0
count = 0
product = 1
while(count<len(number)-12):
	first = int(number[count])
	second = int(number[count+1])
	third = int(number[count+2])
	fourth = int(number[count+3])
	fifth = int(number[count+4])
	sixth = int(number[count+5])
	seventh = int(number[count+6])
	eight = int(number[count+7])
	ninth = int(number[count+8])
	tenth = int(number[count+9])
	eleventh = int(number[count+10])
	twelfth = int(number[count+11])
	thirteenth = int(number[count+12])
	product = first*second*third*fourth*fifth*sixth*seventh*eight*ninth*tenth*eleventh*twelfth     *thirteenth
	if(product>largest):
		largest = product
	count = count + 1
print(largest)
